               <head>Maqāmāt-i Ḥamīdī by Ḥamīd al-Dīn Abū Bakr ʻUmar ibn Maḥmūd, d. 1163 or 4 </head>
               <msContents class="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh85100087">
                  <summary>Adventures in rhymed prose attributed to a friend of the unnamed
                            author, identified as Ḥamīd al-Dīn Abū Bakr ibn ʻUmar ibn Maḥmūd
                            al-Balkhī (d. 559/1164). The work was completed, according to the
                            preface, in Jumādā II 551/1156. </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_600A-item1">
                     <author key="viaf_22109210">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Ḥamīd al-Dīn Abū Bakr ʻUmar ibn
                                    Maḥmūd, d. 1163 or 4 </persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">حمید الدین ابو بکر عمر ابن محمود</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_9380">Maqāmāt-i Ḥamīdī </title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa">مقامات حمیدی</title>
                     <colophon>(<locus>f. 116v</locus>) Completed on 18th Zu ’l-Ḥijjah 1229
                                regnal year 9 of Muḥammad Akbar Shāh (1 December 1814). 
                     </colophon>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                     <filiation>Other copies in the British Library: Rieu p. 747 <ref target="https://archive.org/details/gri_33125008986313/page/747/mode/1up" type="n/a">Add MS 7620</ref>, and <ref target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_5448">Or
                                    11984</ref>. 
                     </filiation>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
